videos.description: Needing a win the clinch their division, Wayne Gallman puts Clemson up early with a 42-yard touchdown run for a 7-0 lead on Wake Forest.
videos.headline: Gallman jump starts Clemson with 42-yard TD run

videos.description: Deshaun Watson takes the snap and on the designed run sweeps left into the end zone to double Clemson's lead at 14-0.
videos.headline: Watson gets Clemson back on the board

videos.description: Clemson scores for the third time on its third possession when Deshaun Watson hits Mike Williams for the 15-yard strike to put the Tigers up 21-0.
videos.headline: Williams' awesome catch has Clemson up big early

videos.description: On the keeper, Deshaun Watson slips passed the defender and scores putting Clemson up 28-0 early in the second quarter over Wake Forest.
videos.headline: Watson rushes in for second TD of the game

videos.description: Dom Maggio punt for 43 yds , Ray-Ray McCloud returns for 2 yds to the Clem 27 Ray-Ray McCloud fumbled, recovered by WFrst
videos.headline: Wake Forest recovers fumble on punt

videos.description: Wake Forest's Cade Carney goes outside with the handoff and rather than going around the defender, decides to go over him with an awesome hurdle to pick up the first down.
videos.headline: Carney skies over defender with awesome hurdle

videos.description: After jumping out to a 28-0 lead, Wake Forest was clawing back with 13 unanswered points until Wayne Gallman punches it in from a yard out to put Clemson up 35-13 in the fourth quarter.
videos.headline: Gallman scores again to calm Clemson's nerves
